mysql: SELECT count(`authors`.`id`) AS `count` FROM `authors` AS `authors` LEFT OUTER JOIN `books` AS `books` ON `authors`.`id` = `books`.`authors_id` LEFT OUTER JOIN `reviews` AS `books.reviews` ON `books`.`id` = `books.reviews`.`books_id` INNER JOIN `publishers_books` AS `books.publishers_books` ON `books`.`id` = `books.publishers_books`.`books_id` WHERE (`authors`.`id` >= 0 AND `authors`.`id` < 10) AND (`authors`.`name` != 'Bob' OR `authors`.`name` != 'Alice')
postgresql: SELECT count("authors"."id") AS "count" FROM "authors" AS "authors" LEFT OUTER JOIN "books" AS "books" ON "authors"."id" = "books"."authors_id" LEFT OUTER JOIN "reviews" AS "books.reviews" ON "books"."id" = "books.reviews"."books_id" INNER JOIN "publishers_books" AS "books.publishers_books" ON "books"."id" = "books.publishers_books"."books_id" WHERE ("authors"."id" >= 0 AND "authors"."id" < 10) AND ("authors"."name" != 'Bob' OR "authors"."name" != 'Alice')
